        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 1:24PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 123 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles north of Spartanburg to 10 miles east
of Greenville Downtown. Movement was east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible as well as
the possibilitity of hail accumulation on the ground.

Locations impacted include...
Reidville, Moore, Wellford, USC Upstate, Roebuck, Woodruff,
Spartanburg, Cedar Springs, Boiling Springs SC, and Duncan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
